{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos975.erdos_975 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos975.erdos_975.","id":"vf_46fc737df36c7149","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #975: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $f\\in \\mathbb{Z}[x]$ be an irreducible non-constant polynomial such that $f(n)\\geq 1$ for all large $n\\in\\mathbb{N}$. Does there exist a constant $c=c(f)>0$ such that\\[\\sum_{n\\leq X} \\tau(f(n))\\sim cX\\log X,\\]where $\\tau$ is the divisor function? Current best: Van der Corput \\cite{Va39} proved that\\[\\sum_{n\\leq X} \\tau(f(n))\\gg_f X\\log X.\\]Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er52b} proved using elementary methods that\\[\\sum_{n\\leq X} \\tau(f(n))\\ll_f X\\log X.\\]Such an asymptotic formula is known whenever $f$ is an irreducible quadratic, as proved by Hooley \\cite{Ho63}. For example,\\[\\sum_{n\\leq x}\\tau(n^2+1)=\\frac{3}{\\pi}x\\log x+O(x).\\]Tao has a blog post on this topic. Prize: no. OEIS: A147807. Tags: divisors, number theory.","id":"vf_8a7fcdd656a78c84","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/975.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_46fc737df36c7149","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:975","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_46fc737df36c7149","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_8a7fcdd656a78c84","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred